##China 1958 Afforestation Campaign S27
The Ministry of Forestry continued in administering nationwide afforestation, forest management and production of forest products through its ten departments and bureaus. It adopted the administrative system of the former Soviet Union but with little effort to integrate with China’s domestic situation. This resulted in an inevitable administrative dichotomy between forest harvesting and forest cultivation. 

On 11 February 1958, the 1st National People’s Congress decided to merge the Ministry of Forest Industry and the Ministry of Forestry, and to set up constituent departments and bureaus based on the responsibilities of the two former ministries.

